{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":721,"text":"I work with children with autism."},{"time":3391,"text":"Specifically, I make technologies"},{"time":5305,"text":"to help them communicate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":7476,"text":"Now, many of the problems that children"},{"time":9015,"text":"with autism face, they have a common source,"},{"time":12778,"text":"and that source is that they find it difficult"},{"time":14872,"text":"to understand abstraction, symbolism."},{"time":20132,"text":"And because of this, they have \na lot of difficulty with language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24784,"text":"Let me tell you a little bit about why this is."},{"time":27799,"text":"You see that this is a picture of a bowl of soup."},{"time":31733,"text":"All of us can see it. All of us understand this."},{"time":34218,"text":"These are two other pictures of soup,"},{"time":36530,"text":"but you can see that these are more abstract"},{"time":38597,"text":"These are not quite as concrete."},{"time":40453,"text":"And when you get to language,"},{"time":42627,"text":"you see that it becomes a word"},{"time":44495,"text":"whose look, the way it looks and the way it sounds,"},{"time":47756,"text":"has absolutely nothing to do \nwith what it started with,"},{"time":50668,"text":"or what it represents, which is the bowl of soup."},{"time":53498,"text":"So it's essentially a completely abstract,"},{"time":56398,"text":"a completely arbitrary representation of something"},{"time":58974,"text":"which is in the real world,"},{"time":60137,"text":"and this is something that children with autism"},{"time":61928,"text":"have an incredible amount of difficulty with."},{"time":65092,"text":"Now that's why most of the people \nthat work with children with autism --"},{"time":67843,"text":"speech therapists, educators --"},{"time":69721,"text":"what they do is, they try to help children with autism"},{"time":72354,"text":"communicate not with words, but with pictures."},{"time":75583,"text":"So if a child with autism wanted to say,"},{"time":77513,"text":"\"I want soup,\" that child would pick"},{"time":79971,"text":"three different pictures, \"I,\" \"want,\" and \"soup,\""},{"time":82231,"text":"and they would put these together,"},{"time":83840,"text":"and then the therapist or the parent would"},{"time":85707,"text":"understand that this is what the kid wants to say."},{"time":87594,"text":"And this has been incredibly effective;"},{"time":89372,"text":"for the last 30, 40 years"},{"time":91513,"text":"people have been doing this."},{"time":93126,"text":"In fact, a few years back,"},{"time":94475,"text":"I developed an app for the iPad"},{"time":97150,"text":"which does exactly this. It's called Avaz,"},{"time":99405,"text":"and the way it works is that kids select"},{"time":101684,"text":"different pictures."},{"time":103005,"text":"These pictures are sequenced\ntogether to form sentences,"},{"time":105575,"text":"and these sentences are spoken out."},{"time":107294,"text":"So Avaz is essentially converting pictures,"},{"time":110319,"text":"it's a translator, it converts pictures into speech."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114279,"text":"Now, this was very effective."},{"time":115997,"text":"There are thousands of children using this,"},{"time":117381,"text":"you know, all over the world,"},{"time":118811,"text":"and I started thinking about"},{"time":120986,"text":"what it does and what it doesn't do."},{"time":123640,"text":"And I realized something interesting:"},{"time":125324,"text":"Avaz helps children with autism learn words."},{"time":129527,"text":"What it doesn't help them do is to learn"},{"time":131932,"text":"word patterns."},{"time":134680,"text":"Let me explain this in a little more detail."},{"time":137152,"text":"Take this sentence: \"I want soup tonight.\""},{"time":140209,"text":"Now it's not just the words\nhere that convey the meaning."},{"time":144289,"text":"It's also the way in which these words are arranged,"},{"time":147429,"text":"the way these words are modified and arranged."},{"time":149959,"text":"And that's why a sentence like \"I want soup tonight\""},{"time":152265,"text":"is different from a sentence like"},{"time":154249,"text":"\"Soup want I tonight,\" which \nis completely meaningless."},{"time":157561,"text":"So there is another hidden abstraction here"},{"time":160180,"text":"which children with autism find\na lot of difficulty coping with,"},{"time":163737,"text":"and that's the fact that you can modify words"},{"time":166577,"text":"and you can arrange them to have"},{"time":168678,"text":"different meanings, to convey different ideas."},{"time":171573,"text":"Now, this is what we call grammar."},{"time":175032,"text":"And grammar is incredibly powerful,"},{"time":177068,"text":"because grammar is this one component of language"},{"time":180225,"text":"which takes this finite vocabulary that all of us have"},{"time":183714,"text":"and allows us to convey an\ninfinite amount of information,"},{"time":188245,"text":"an infinite amount of ideas."},{"time":190379,"text":"It's the way in which you can put things together"},{"time":192381,"text":"in order to convey anything you want to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194549,"text":"And so after I developed Avaz,"},{"time":196676,"text":"I worried for a very long time"},{"time":198244,"text":"about how I could give grammar \nto children with autism."},{"time":202154,"text":"The solution came to me from\na very interesting perspective."},{"time":204429,"text":"I happened to chance upon a child with autism"},{"time":207878,"text":"conversing with her mom,"},{"time":209987,"text":"and this is what happened."},{"time":212081,"text":"Completely out of the blue, very spontaneously,"},{"time":214267,"text":"the child got up and said, \"Eat.\""},{"time":216730,"text":"Now what was interesting was"},{"time":218500,"text":"the way in which the mom was trying to tease out"},{"time":222744,"text":"the meaning of what the child wanted to say"},{"time":224957,"text":"by talking to her in questions."},{"time":227217,"text":"So she asked, \"Eat what? Do \nyou want to eat ice cream?"},{"time":229810,"text":"You want to eat? Somebody else wants to eat?"},{"time":231922,"text":"You want to eat cream now? You\nwant to eat ice cream in the evening?\""},{"time":235235,"text":"And then it struck me that"},{"time":236749,"text":"what the mother had done was something incredible."},{"time":238777,"text":"She had been able to get that child to communicate"},{"time":240771,"text":"an idea to her without grammar."},{"time":244909,"text":"And it struck me that maybe this is what"},{"time":247605,"text":"I was looking for."},{"time":248990,"text":"Instead of arranging words in an order, in sequence,"},{"time":253132,"text":"as a sentence, you arrange them"},{"time":255304,"text":"in this map, where they're all linked together"},{"time":259115,"text":"not by placing them one after the other"},{"time":261258,"text":"but in questions, in question-answer pairs."},{"time":264542,"text":"And so if you do this, then what you're conveying"},{"time":266900,"text":"is not a sentence in English,"},{"time":268886,"text":"but what you're conveying is really a meaning,"},{"time":271852,"text":"the meaning of a sentence in English."},{"time":273363,"text":"Now, meaning is really the underbelly,\nin some sense, of language."},{"time":276295,"text":"It's what comes after thought but before language."},{"time":280116,"text":"And the idea was that this particular representation"},{"time":282619,"text":"might convey meaning in its raw form."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285880,"text":"So I was very excited by this, you know,"},{"time":287651,"text":"hopping around all over the place,"},{"time":289144,"text":"trying to figure out if I can convert"},{"time":290915,"text":"all possible sentences that I hear into this."},{"time":293439,"text":"And I found that this is not enough."},{"time":295212,"text":"Why is this not enough?"},{"time":296597,"text":"This is not enough because if you wanted to convey"},{"time":298308,"text":"something like negation,"},{"time":300558,"text":"you want to say, \"I don't want soup,\""},{"time":302294,"text":"then you can't do that by asking a question."},{"time":304514,"text":"You do that by changing the word \"want.\""},{"time":306799,"text":"Again, if you wanted to say,"},{"time":308436,"text":"\"I wanted soup yesterday,\""},{"time":310416,"text":"you do that by converting\nthe word \"want\" into \"wanted.\""},{"time":313153,"text":"It's a past tense."},{"time":314819,"text":"So this is a flourish which I added"},{"time":316922,"text":"to make the system complete."},{"time":318498,"text":"This is a map of words joined together"},{"time":320475,"text":"as questions and answers,"},{"time":322131,"text":"and with these filters applied on top of them"},{"time":324395,"text":"in order to modify them to represent"},{"time":326212,"text":"certain nuances."},{"time":327921,"text":"Let me show you this with a different example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329872,"text":"Let's take this sentence:"},{"time":331126,"text":"\"I told the carpenter I could not pay him.\""},{"time":333106,"text":"It's a fairly complicated sentence."},{"time":334898,"text":"The way that this particular system works,"},{"time":336791,"text":"you can start with any part of this sentence."},{"time":339369,"text":"I'm going to start with the word \"tell.\""},{"time":341067,"text":"So this is the word \"tell.\""},{"time":342529,"text":"Now this happened in the past,"},{"time":344129,"text":"so I'm going to make that \"told.\""},{"time":346352,"text":"Now, what I'm going to do is,"},{"time":348060,"text":"I'm going to ask questions."},{"time":349816,"text":"So, who told? I told."},{"time":352180,"text":"I told whom? I told the carpenter."},{"time":354107,"text":"Now we start with a different part of the sentence."},{"time":355858,"text":"We start with the word \"pay,\""},{"time":357725,"text":"and we add the ability filter to it to make it \"can pay.\""},{"time":362302,"text":"Then we make it \"can't pay,\""},{"time":364403,"text":"and we can make it \"couldn't pay\""},{"time":366002,"text":"by making it the past tense."},{"time":367665,"text":"So who couldn't pay? I couldn't pay."},{"time":369588,"text":"Couldn't pay whom? I couldn't pay the carpenter."},{"time":372264,"text":"And then you join these two together"},{"time":373995,"text":"by asking this question:"},{"time":375345,"text":"What did I tell the carpenter?"},{"time":377082,"text":"I told the carpenter I could not pay him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381131,"text":"Now think about this. This is"},{"time":383068,"text":"—(Applause)—"},{"time":386610,"text":"this is a representation of this sentence"},{"time":390282,"text":"without language."},{"time":392717,"text":"And there are two or three\ninteresting things about this."},{"time":394909,"text":"First of all, I could have started anywhere."},{"time":398040,"text":"I didn't have to start with the word \"tell.\""},{"time":400283,"text":"I could have started anywhere in the sentence,"},{"time":401699,"text":"and I could have made this entire thing."},{"time":403206,"text":"The second thing is, if I wasn't an English speaker,"},{"time":405982,"text":"if I was speaking in some other language,"},{"time":408157,"text":"this map would actually hold true in any language."},{"time":411313,"text":"So long as the questions are standardized,"},{"time":413303,"text":"the map is actually independent of language."},{"time":417590,"text":"So I call this FreeSpeech,"},{"time":419705,"text":"and I was playing with this for many, many months."},{"time":422640,"text":"I was trying out so many\ndifferent combinations of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425366,"text":"And then I noticed something very\ninteresting about FreeSpeech."},{"time":427655,"text":"I was trying to convert language,"},{"time":430898,"text":"convert sentences in English\ninto sentences in FreeSpeech,"},{"time":433282,"text":"and vice versa, and back and forth."},{"time":435034,"text":"And I realized that this particular configuration,"},{"time":437289,"text":"this particular way of representing language,"},{"time":439315,"text":"it allowed me to actually create very concise rules"},{"time":443710,"text":"that go between FreeSpeech on one side"},{"time":446444,"text":"and English on the other."},{"time":447932,"text":"So I could actually write this set of rules"},{"time":450112,"text":"that translates from this particular\nrepresentation into English."},{"time":453507,"text":"And so I developed this thing."},{"time":455338,"text":"I developed this thing called \nthe FreeSpeech Engine"},{"time":457570,"text":"which takes any FreeSpeech sentence as the input"},{"time":460131,"text":"and gives out perfectly grammatical English text."},{"time":464061,"text":"And by putting these two pieces together,"},{"time":465666,"text":"the representation and the engine,"},{"time":467547,"text":"I was able to create an app, a\ntechnology for children with autism,"},{"time":471343,"text":"that not only gives them words"},{"time":473842,"text":"but also gives them grammar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477783,"text":"So I tried this out with kids with autism,"},{"time":480143,"text":"and I found that there was an \nincredible amount of identification."},{"time":485156,"text":"They were able to create sentences in FreeSpeech"},{"time":487876,"text":"which were much more complicated\nbut much more effective"},{"time":490434,"text":"than equivalent sentences in English,"},{"time":493333,"text":"and I started thinking about"},{"time":495015,"text":"why that might be the case."},{"time":496984,"text":"And I had an idea, and I want to \ntalk to you about this idea next."},{"time":501271,"text":"In about 1997, about 15 years back,"},{"time":504413,"text":"there were a group of scientists that were trying"},{"time":506424,"text":"to understand how the brain processes language,"},{"time":508813,"text":"and they found something very interesting."},{"time":510592,"text":"They found that when you learn a language"},{"time":512464,"text":"as a child, as a two-year-old,"},{"time":515376,"text":"you learn it with a certain part of your brain,"},{"time":517742,"text":"and when you learn a language as an adult --"},{"time":519342,"text":"for example, if I wanted to\nlearn Japanese right now —"},{"time":523253,"text":"a completely different part of my brain is used."},{"time":525960,"text":"Now I don't know why that's the case,"},{"time":527791,"text":"but my guess is that that's because"},{"time":529782,"text":"when you learn a language as an adult,"},{"time":532219,"text":"you almost invariably learn it"},{"time":533835,"text":"through your native language, or\nthrough your first language."},{"time":538101,"text":"So what's interesting about FreeSpeech"},{"time":541353,"text":"is that when you create a sentence"},{"time":543155,"text":"or when you create language,"},{"time":544850,"text":"a child with autism creates\nlanguage with FreeSpeech,"},{"time":547920,"text":"they're not using this support language,"},{"time":549753,"text":"they're not using this bridge language."},{"time":551964,"text":"They're directly constructing the sentence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554621,"text":"And so this gave me this idea."},{"time":556814,"text":"Is it possible to use FreeSpeech"},{"time":558838,"text":"not for children with autism"},{"time":561348,"text":"but to teach language to people without disabilities?"},{"time":567610,"text":"And so I tried a number of experiments."},{"time":569588,"text":"The first thing I did was I built a jigsaw puzzle"},{"time":572536,"text":"in which these questions and answers"},{"time":574506,"text":"are coded in the form of shapes,"},{"time":576341,"text":"in the form of colors,"},{"time":577479,"text":"and you have people putting these together"},{"time":579328,"text":"and trying to understand how this works."},{"time":581101,"text":"And I built an app out of it, a game out of it,"},{"time":583477,"text":"in which children can play with words"},{"time":586138,"text":"and with a reinforcement,"},{"time":587842,"text":"a sound reinforcement of visual structures,"},{"time":590427,"text":"they're able to learn language."},{"time":592440,"text":"And this, this has a lot of potential, a lot of promise,"},{"time":595176,"text":"and the government of India recently"},{"time":597151,"text":"licensed this technology from us,"},{"time":598555,"text":"and they're going to try it out\nwith millions of different children"},{"time":600629,"text":"trying to teach them English."},{"time":603234,"text":"And the dream, the hope, the vision, really,"},{"time":605848,"text":"is that when they learn English this way,"},{"time":608930,"text":"they learn it with the same proficiency"},{"time":611573,"text":"as their mother tongue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615291,"text":"All right, let's talk about something else."},{"time":619107,"text":"Let's talk about speech."},{"time":621104,"text":"This is speech."},{"time":622375,"text":"So speech is the primary mode of communication"},{"time":624337,"text":"delivered between all of us."},{"time":625950,"text":"Now what's interesting about speech is that"},{"time":627805,"text":"speech is one-dimensional."},{"time":629050,"text":"Why is it one-dimensional?"},{"time":630409,"text":"It's one-dimensional because it's sound."},{"time":631977,"text":"It's also one-dimensional because"},{"time":633516,"text":"our mouths are built that way."},{"time":634721,"text":"Our mouths are built to create\none-dimensional sound."},{"time":638233,"text":"But if you think about the brain,"},{"time":641099,"text":"the thoughts that we have in our heads"},{"time":642863,"text":"are not one-dimensional."},{"time":644965,"text":"I mean, we have these rich,"},{"time":646424,"text":"complicated, multi-dimensional ideas."},{"time":649452,"text":"Now, it seems to me that language"},{"time":651142,"text":"is really the brain's invention"},{"time":653474,"text":"to convert this rich, multi-dimensional thought"},{"time":656570,"text":"on one hand"},{"time":658157,"text":"into speech on the other hand."},{"time":660080,"text":"Now what's interesting is that"},{"time":661842,"text":"we do a lot of work in information nowadays,"},{"time":664410,"text":"and almost all of that is done\nin the language domain."},{"time":667489,"text":"Take Google, for example."},{"time":669428,"text":"Google trawls all these\ncountless billions of websites,"},{"time":672105,"text":"all of which are in English,\nand when you want to use Google,"},{"time":674830,"text":"you go into Google search, and you type in English,"},{"time":677280,"text":"and it matches the English with the English."},{"time":681443,"text":"What if we could do this in FreeSpeech instead?"},{"time":685026,"text":"I have a suspicion that if we did this,"},{"time":687327,"text":"we'd find that algorithms like searching,"},{"time":689395,"text":"like retrieval, all of these things,"},{"time":691720,"text":"are much simpler and also more effective,"},{"time":694795,"text":"because they don't process\nthe data structure of speech."},{"time":699212,"text":"Instead they're processing\nthe data structure of thought."},{"time":705188,"text":"The data structure of thought."},{"time":707996,"text":"That's a provocative idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710072,"text":"But let's look at this in a little more detail."},{"time":712214,"text":"So this is the FreeSpeech ecosystem."},{"time":714580,"text":"We have the Free Speech\nrepresentation on one side,"},{"time":717464,"text":"and we have the FreeSpeech \nEngine, which generates English."},{"time":719694,"text":"Now if you think about it,"},{"time":721419,"text":"FreeSpeech, I told you, is completely \nlanguage-independent."},{"time":723963,"text":"It doesn't have any specific information in it"},{"time":726050,"text":"which is about English."},{"time":727278,"text":"So everything that this system knows about English"},{"time":730078,"text":"is actually encoded into the engine."},{"time":734698,"text":"That's a pretty interesting concept in itself."},{"time":736935,"text":"You've encoded an entire human language"},{"time":740539,"text":"into a software program."},{"time":743184,"text":"But if you look at what's inside the engine,"},{"time":745715,"text":"it's actually not very complicated."},{"time":748073,"text":"It's not very complicated code."},{"time":750178,"text":"And what's more interesting is the fact that"},{"time":752850,"text":"the vast majority of the code in that engine"},{"time":755053,"text":"is not really English-specific."},{"time":757465,"text":"And that gives this interesting idea."},{"time":759360,"text":"It might be very easy for us to actually"},{"time":761398,"text":"create these engines in many,\nmany different languages,"},{"time":765224,"text":"in Hindi, in French, in German, in Swahili."},{"time":771578,"text":"And that gives another interesting idea."},{"time":774377,"text":"For example, supposing I was a writer,"},{"time":777031,"text":"say, for a newspaper or for a magazine."},{"time":779153,"text":"I could create content in one language, FreeSpeech,"},{"time":784164,"text":"and the person who's consuming that content,"},{"time":786220,"text":"the person who's reading that particular information"},{"time":789281,"text":"could choose any engine,"},{"time":791776,"text":"and they could read it in their own mother tongue,"},{"time":794512,"text":"in their native language."},{"time":798451,"text":"I mean, this is an incredibly attractive idea,"},{"time":801173,"text":"especially for India."},{"time":803172,"text":"We have so many different languages."},{"time":804862,"text":"There's a song about India, and there's a description"},{"time":807004,"text":"of the country as, it says,"},{"time":809348,"text":"(in Sanskrit)."},{"time":811708,"text":"That means \"ever-smiling speaker"},{"time":814481,"text":"of beautiful languages.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":819000,"text":"Language is beautiful."},{"time":820964,"text":"I think it's the most beautiful of human creations."},{"time":823418,"text":"I think it's the loveliest thing\nthat our brains have invented."},{"time":827396,"text":"It entertains, it educates, it enlightens,"},{"time":830980,"text":"but what I like the most about language"},{"time":833024,"text":"is that it empowers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":834524,"text":"I want to leave you with this."},{"time":836362,"text":"This is a photograph of my collaborators,"},{"time":838747,"text":"my earliest collaborators"},{"time":839744,"text":"when I started working on language"},{"time":841206,"text":"and autism and various other things."},{"time":842708,"text":"The girl's name is Pavna,"},{"time":844125,"text":"and that's her mother, Kalpana."},{"time":846027,"text":"And Pavna's an entrepreneur,"},{"time":848165,"text":"but her story is much more remarkable than mine,"},{"time":850536,"text":"because Pavna is about 23."},{"time":852936,"text":"She has quadriplegic cerebral palsy,"},{"time":855488,"text":"so ever since she was born,"},{"time":857128,"text":"she could neither move nor talk."},{"time":860728,"text":"And everything that she's accomplished so far,"},{"time":863131,"text":"finishing school, going to college,"},{"time":865358,"text":"starting a company,"},{"time":866774,"text":"collaborating with me to develop Avaz,"},{"time":868914,"text":"all of these things she's done"},{"time":870806,"text":"with nothing more than moving her eyes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":876329,"text":"Daniel Webster said this:"},{"time":879018,"text":"He said, \"If all of my possessions were taken"},{"time":881958,"text":"from me with one exception,"},{"time":884946,"text":"I would choose to keep the power of communication,"},{"time":887927,"text":"for with it, I would regain all the rest.\""},{"time":891830,"text":"And that's why, of all of these incredible \napplications of FreeSpeech,"},{"time":896946,"text":"the one that's closest to my heart"},{"time":899026,"text":"still remains the ability for this"},{"time":901094,"text":"to empower children with disabilities"},{"time":903474,"text":"to be able to communicate,"},{"time":905247,"text":"the power of communication,"},{"time":907036,"text":"to get back all the rest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":909276,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":910673,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":912005,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":916204,"text":"Thank you. Thank you. Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":921527,"text":"Thank you. Thank you. Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}